Candidate Cross-Match¶

Cross match candidates to the Legacy Survey DR10.

Legacy Survey overview: https://datalab.noirlab.edu/ls/ls.php

Tractor catalog schema: https://datalab.noirlab.edu/query.php?name=ls_dr10.tractor

For catalog units: https://www.legacysurvey.org/dr10/catalogs/https://www.legacysurvey.org/dr10/catalogs/

For cutouts: https://www.legacysurvey.org/viewer/cutout.jpg?ra=7.5334&dec=-43.4581&layer=ls-dr9&pixscale=0.06

Cross match.¶

Match with a star means there is a star within a radius of 2 times the PSF, in r-band.

If there is a match with a star, it's a star, end of story. Potential nearby extended objects are not saved.

If it is NOT matched with a star, then nearby extended objects within a radius of 3 times their half-light radius are considered.

If there is a match with an extended object, take the one that is closest in HLR.

If the offset between candidate and extended object is less than the PSF, the candidate is flagged as a potential nuclear source.

In [16]:
verbose = False

# 0 if nothing within 72 arcsec; otherwise the number of nearby things
cand_region_pop = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='int')

# -1 if no match; otherwise, the index in the dr10 array
cand_match_idx = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='int') - 1

# -1 if no info; 0 if galaxy; 1 if star
cand_match_star = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='int') - 1

# 1 if galaxy and potentially nuclear; 0 otherwise
cand_match_gnuc = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='int')

# value of the offset in arcsec
cand_match_offset = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='float')

for c, coord in enumerate(cand_coords):
    ralo = cand_ra[c] - 0.02
    rahi = cand_ra[c] + 0.02
    delo = cand_dec[c] - 0.02
    dehi = cand_dec[c] + 0.02
    tx = np.where((dr10_ra > ralo) & (dr10_ra < rahi) & 
                  (dr10_dec > delo) & (dr10_dec < dehi))[0]
    del ralo, rahi, delo, dehi
    
    cand_region_pop[c] = len(tx)
    
    if len(tx) > 0:
    
        off_sky = coord.separation(dr10_coords[tx]).arcsec
        off_psf = off_sky / dr10_psfsize_r[tx]
        off_hlr = off_sky / dr10_shape_r[tx]

        sx = np.where((off_psf < 2) & (dr10_type[tx] == 'PSF'))[0]
        gx = np.where((off_hlr < 5) & (dr10_type[tx] != 'PSF'))[0]
    
        if verbose:
            if (len(sx) > 0) | (len(gx) > 0):
                print(' ')
                print(cand_id[c], cand_ra[c], cand_dec[c])
                print(cand_LSlink[c])
                print(cand_DVlink[c])
                print(len(sx), len(gx))
                if len(sx) > 0:
                    for x in sx:
                        print('star ', x, tx[x], dr10_type[tx[x]], off_sky[x], off_psf[x], off_hlr[x], 
                              dr10_psfsize_r[tx[x]], dr10_shape_r[tx[x]], dr10_mag_r[tx[x]])
                if len(gx) > 0:
                    for x in gx:
                        print('gal ', x, tx[x], dr10_type[tx[x]], off_sky[x], off_psf[x], off_hlr[x], 
                              dr10_psfsize_r[tx[x]], dr10_shape_r[tx[x]], dr10_mag_r[tx[x]])

        if (len(sx) > 0) & (cand_match_idx[c] < 0):
            if len(sx) == 1:
                cand_match_idx[c] = tx[sx[0]]
                cand_match_star[c] = 1
                cand_match_offset[c] = off_sky[sx[0]]
            else: 
                mx = np.argmin(off_psf[sx])
                cand_match_idx[c] = tx[sx[mx]]
                cand_match_star[c] = 1
                cand_match_offset[c] = off_sky[sx[mx]]
                del mx

        if (len(gx) > 0) & (cand_match_idx[c] < 0):
            if len(gx) == 1:
                cand_match_idx[c] = tx[gx[0]]
                cand_match_star[c] = 0
                if off_sky[gx[0]] < dr10_psfsize_r[tx[gx[0]]]:
                    cand_match_gnuc[c] = 1
                cand_match_offset[c] = off_sky[gx[0]]
            else:
                mx = np.argmin(off_hlr[gx])
                cand_match_idx[c] = tx[gx[mx]]
                cand_match_star[c] = 0
                if off_sky[gx[mx]] < dr10_psfsize_r[tx[gx[mx]]]:
                    cand_match_gnuc[c] = 1
                cand_match_offset[c] = off_sky[gx[mx]]
                del mx

        if verbose:
            if (len(sx) > 0) | (len(gx) > 0):
                    print(cand_region_pop[c], cand_match_idx[c], cand_match_star[c], cand_match_gnuc[c])
    del tx

Get photo-z from DR9.¶

Set up to query the DR9 tractor table and join to the photoz table.

Only interested in returning NON stars here, so we can cross-match with DR10 galaxies matched to candidates.

In [18]:
query = 'SELECT dr9.ra, dr9.dec, pz.z_phot_mean, pz.z_phot_std, pz.z_spec ' + \
        'FROM ls_dr9.tractor_s AS dr9 ' + \
        'JOIN ls_dr9.photo_z AS pz ON pz.ls_id = dr9.ls_id ' + \
        'WHERE (ra > '+str(cb_ralo)+' AND ra < '+str(cb_rahi)+' AND ' + \
        'dec > '+str(cb_delo)+' AND dec < '+str(cb_dehi)+') '\
        'OR (ra > '+str(eb_ralo)+' AND ra < '+str(eb_rahi)+' AND ' + \
        'dec > '+str(eb_delo)+' AND dec < '+str(eb_dehi)+')'

Cross match PZ to candidates matched to DR10 galaxies¶

In [23]:
cand_dr9_zphot_mean = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='float') - 99.
cand_dr9_zphot_std = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='float') - 99.
cand_dr9_zspec = np.zeros(len(cand_id), dtype='float') - 99.

for c in range(len(cand_id)):
    if cand_match_star[c] == 0:
        host_ra = dr10_ra[cand_match_idx[c]]
        host_dec = dr10_dec[cand_match_idx[c]]
        tx = np.where((np.abs(dr9_ra - host_ra) < 0.02) & 
                      (np.abs(dr9_dec - host_dec) < 0.02))[0]
        if len(tx) > 0:
            coord_host = SkyCoord(host_ra, host_dec, unit="deg")
            coords_dr9 = SkyCoord(dr9_ra[tx], dr9_dec[tx], unit="deg")
            offsets = coord_host.separation(coords_dr9).arcsec
            ox = np.argmin(offsets)
            if offsets[ox] <= 2.0:
                cand_dr9_zphot_mean[c] = dr9_zphot_mean[tx[ox]]
                cand_dr9_zphot_std[c] = dr9_zphot_std[tx[ox]]
                cand_dr9_zspec[c] = dr9_zspec[tx[ox]]
            del ox, offsets, coords_dr9, coord_host
        del host_ra, host_dec, tx

    else:

                   '%5i %2i %2i %5.1f '\

                   '%5s %6.2f '\
                   '%10.6f %10.6f %10.6f '\
                   '%10.6f %10.6f %10.6f '\
                   '%9.4f %9.4f %9.4f \n' % 
                   (cand_id[c], cand_ra[c], cand_dec[c], 
                    cand_region_pop[c], cand_match_star[c], cand_match_gnuc[c], -99., 
                    -99., -99., -99., -99, 
                    -99., -99., -99., 
                    'xxx', -99., 
                    -99., -99., -99., 
                    -99., -99., -99., 
                    -99., -99., -99.))
